Atlantic City is a 1980 French-Canadian romantic crime film directed by Louis Malle .
Filmed in late 1979 , it was released in France and Germany in 1980 and in the United States in 1981 .
The script was written by John Guare .
It stars Burt Lancaster , Susan Sarandon , Kate Reid , Robert Joy , Hollis McLaren , Michel Piccoli , and Al Waxman .
Atlantic City is among the 41 films to be nominated for all `` Big Five '' Academy Awards , including Best Picture , Best Director , Best Actor , Best Actress and Best Screenplay , and one of only eight among this group to not take home a single award .